    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There are problems using this lib:\r\nit uses handlebar template files that are in the repo, these need to be loaded on runtime which won't fly in our webpack situation. We could put the templates in localstorage on load and rig fs to point to browserfs but then we'd point the fs to the wrong storage basically which could cause other modules to do crazy things. Pointing FS to the fs actually used by remix would be correct. But putting them in indexeddb is not an option because indexeddb is async and this lib uses sync reading for some strange reason - which is not necessary it seems. The best strategy is write our own version based on this idea. I would not put this in the project right now.\r\nPutting the templates in our source is the best way forward. And then rewrite template loader of the generator. ",
